 <p style=\"margin:0 0 14px;font-size:12px;color:#1e3a8a;line-height:1.6;\"><strong>Sell:</strong> 0.315 AVGO shares at market open (at ~$461 if −5% AH gap)<br><strong>Gross P&amp;L:</strong> +$15.42 at $461 | Commission: −$6.00 | Net: +$9.42<br><strong>Buy:</strong> ~0.10 ASML at ~$879 (~$87.90) from freed proceeds<br><strong>Why:</strong> ASML is the EUV monopoly with zero Taiwan geo risk. NVDA's Computex PC chip launch drives more TSMC orders = more ASML EUV machines. Replaces AVGO event risk with ASML structural demand story.<br><strong>Risk:</strong> Missing AVGO recovery; ASML has no near-term catalyst for 6 weeks. Round-trip cost: $12.<br><em>Your call.</em></p>\n          <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#1e40af;\">Option B — TSM → ASML when TSM clears $445</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:12px;color:#1e3a8a;line-height:1.6;\"><strong>Sell:</strong> 0.224 TSM (full exit) at $445 → $99.68 freed<br><strong>Gross P&amp;L:</strong> +$12.70 | Commission: −$6.00 | Net: +$6.70<br><strong>Buy:</strong> ~0.107 ASML at $879 (~$94.05; −$6 buy commission = $88.05 effective deploy)<br><strong>Why:</strong> TSM is HIGH risk (52/100) on geo binary. ASML captures same foundry demand thesis without Taiwan tail risk. TSM TP1 is hit — thesis partially complete.<br><strong>Risk:</strong> Missing TSM upside to TP2 ($485) if geo risk stays latent. Net round-trip: $12.<br><em>Your call. Verify ASML halal status on Musaffa before executing.</em></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr></table>\n    </td></tr>\n\n    <!-- INTELLIGENCE LAYER -->\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:0 24px 24px;\">\n      <p style=\"margin:0 0 12px;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;\">🔍 Intelligence Layer</p>\n      <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"background:#fffbeb;border:1px solid #fde68a;border-left:4px solid #f59e0b;border-radius:8px;\"><tr>\n        <td style=\"padding:16px 20px;\">\n          <p style=\"margin:0 0 8px;font-size:11px;color:#92400e;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;font-weight:600;\">Top Screener Candidates</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:0 0 16px;font-size:13px;color:#111827;line-height:1.7;\">\n            <strong>ASML</strong> — Valuation gap + growth trajectory + NVDA Computex catalyst (more PC chips → more TSMC foundry demand → more EUV machines). Eliminates Taiwan geo risk while preserving AI capex exposure. Tier A halal pre-vetted.<br>\n            <strong>MSFT</strong> — Valuation reasonable (35× fwd for 20%+ growth) + Azure AI growth + catalyst (co-developed N1X chip with NVDA, announced today; FY4Q earnings late July). Best diversifier away from pure-play semi concentration. AAOIFI compliant.<br>\n            <strong>MRVL</strong> — Momentum catalyst (Jensen Huang called it \"next trillion-dollar company\" at Computex, +25% today). Custom ASIC networking for hyperscalers. High beta. ⚠️ Needs fresh halal verification before purchase — not in pre-vetted pool.\n          </p>\n          <p style=\"margin:0 0 8px;font-size:11px;color:#92400e;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;font-weight:600;\">Risk Scores</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:0 0 12px;font-size:12px;color:#374151;line-height:2.1;font-family:'Courier New',monospace;\">\n            NVDA  | 28/100 | LOW      | Post-earnings momentum; Computex TAM expansion; TP1 $240 approaching<br>\n            LLY   | 36/100 | MODERATE | Foundayo launch priced in; low correlation to AI trade; next catalyst TBD<br>\n            AVGO  | 42/100 | MODERATE | Earnings binary tonight ±8%; TP1 hit; strong AI demand offsetting event risk<br>\n            TSM   | 52/100 | HIGH     | Taiwan Strait binary tail risk; TP1 hit; commission blocks trim at current price<br>\n            AMD   | 28/100 | LOW      | Up 20%+ from entry; Seaport upgrade; next catalyst Q2 earnings Aug 4\n          </p>\n          <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:12px;color:#92400e;\"><strong>Concentration note:</strong> Semis (NVDA+AVGO+TSM+AMD) = 80.7% of invested portfolio. NVDA alone = 40.6% (below 45% limit). No breach, but sector concentration is high — any new deployment should lean non-semi (LLY add, MSFT, ASML).</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr></table>\n    </td></tr>\n\n    <!-- WHAT TO DO TOMORROW -->\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:0 24px 24px;\">\n      <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:8px;\"><tr>\n        <td style=\"padding:16px 20px;\">\n          <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#166534;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;\">What to do tomorrow</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:6px 0 0;font-size:14px;color:#14532d;line-height:1.6;\">\n            <strong>1. AVGO (critical):</strong> Check AH reaction at 1 AM Kuwait. If AH &lt;−5%, set limit sell at open. If AH &gt;+5%, plan TP2 trim at $536.<br>\n            <strong>2. NVDA TP1 watch:</strong> If NVDA pushes toward $240 — note that the 30% trim (0.414 shares) would net only +$3.36 after $6 commission ($9.36 gross). Thin. Consider waiting for TP2 at $260 where the 40% trim (0.552 shares × $42.60 gain = $23.52 gross, net +$17.52) is far more compelling.<br>\n            <strong>3. TSM level:</strong> Watch for TSM &gt;$441.93 — that's the gross-$6 threshold for a partial trim.\n          </p>\n        </td>\n      </tr></table>\n    </td></tr>\n\n    <!-- EDUCATION MODULE -->\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:0 24px 24px;\">\n      <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"background:#f1f5f9;border-radius:8px;\"><tr>\n        <td style=\"padding:20px 24px;\">\n          <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;\">📚 Today you learned</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:8px 0 0;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;\">Options-Implied Move</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:12px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#1e293b;line-height:1.7;\">The options market on AVGO tonight is pricing ±8%. Here's how that number is extracted: add the at-the-money call and put prices for the nearest expiry (June 4). If that straddle costs ~$39 with AVGO at $487, the implied move is $39/$487 ≈ ±8%. This isn't a prediction — it's what the market is charging to hedge. What matters for your AVGO hold: to make money by being long through earnings, AVGO has to move <em>more</em> than the +8% already priced in. A solid beat with in-line guidance? Market already expected that — stock may open +4% and feel like a win while actually being a slight disappointment relative to implied expectations. Tonight: watch the after-hours magnitude vs that 8% bar. If AVGO opens up only +3%, the options market won, and the reaction is softer than the consensus bull case assumed.</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:12px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;font-style:italic;\">Also today: <strong>IV crush</strong> — after earnings print, implied volatility collapses regardless of direction. Every AVGO option gets cheaper at 5:01 PM ET tonight, even if the stock moves 12%. That's why buying options into earnings is a structurally hard trade — you need the move to exceed the IV crush.</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr></table>\n    </td></tr>\n\n    <!-- FOOTER -->\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:16px 24px 24px;border-top:1px solid #f3f4f6;\">\n      <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.5;\">Research output, not financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Verify halal compliance quarterly on Zoya or Musaffa. Price data: NVDA = June 3 intraday (CNBC ~4 PM ET); LLY/AVGO/TSM/AMD = June 2 confirmed closes. Generated June 3, 2026 at 11:05 PM Kuwait time (AST, UTC+3).</p>\n    </td></tr>\n\n  </table>\n  </td></tr>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>"
